            Submitted by Peter M. on Sun, 06/04/2025 - 08:10
            In reply to by
            Permalink
              Hello Sandy Nguyen,
              The question is which word 'enough' applies to in the sentence. If you say enough natural beauty then you are saying there is some natural beauty but there needs to be more. If you say natural enough beauty you are saying that there is beauty but it needs to be more natural. Since it's hard to make a town's beauty 'more natural' I think the first answer is clearly the right option.
              Peter
              The LearnEnglish Team
